objects.name: busy buzzard
objects.description: A plugin-based Windows remote access tool that provides the capability to load and execute shellcode or Windows DLL plugins.

objects.description: A cybersecurity company that has reported on the Busy Buzzard malware.

objects.name: PwC
objects.description: A professional services company that has reported on the Busy Buzzard malware.

objects.name: VMware
objects.description: A company that provides virtualization software, which is targeted by the Busy Buzzard malware for anti-analysis techniques.

objects.name: ChChes
objects.description: A threat actor that has been associated with a similar User-Agent string to the one used by the Busy Buzzard malware.

objects.name: T1129
objects.description: Shared Modules: The adversary is using the LoadLibraryW and GetProcAddress API functions to load additional modules and execute functions from them.

objects.name: T1106
objects.description: Native API: The adversary is using the VirtualAlloc and CreateThread API functions to inject and execute shellcode plugins.

objects.name: T1055.009
objects.description: Process Injection: Proc Memory: The adversary is injecting the malware into the memory of a process, with additional shellcode modules also injected into the memory of the same process.

objects.name: T1497.001
objects.description: Virtualization/Sandbox Evasion: System Checks: The adversary is testing the Windows Registry for the presence of a key associated with VMware.

objects.name: T1083
objects.description: File and Directory Discovery: The adversary is providing the capability to browse files and directories.

objects.name: T1082
objects.description: System Information Discovery: The adversary is providing the capability to gather system information.

objects.name: T1016
objects.description: System Network Configuration Discovery: The adversary is gathering information about the system's network configuration.

objects.name: T1124
objects.description: Command and Control: The adversary is using command and control channels to communicate with the compromised system.

objects.name: T1071.001
objects.description: Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols: The adversary is using web protocols for command and control communications.

objects.name: T1095
objects.description: Non-Application Layer Protocol: The adversary is using non-application layer protocols for command and control communications.

objects.name: T1573
objects.description: Encrypted Channel: The adversary is using encrypted channels for command and control communications.
